On this last day of Black History Month, I'm honoring my late-father, Robert Graves. 

He was a winner both on and off the basketball court during his 20 seasons as head coach at Central High School in Louisville, Ky.

He coached Central to seven Sixth Region titles and two KHSAA Sweet 16 state championships – 1969 and 1974– during his time as the Yellowjackets’ head man.

Also, he was also a crusader for equal rights and justice during the period of 1965-85 when he led Central to a record of 445 wins and 116 losses. Gone but not forgotten. RIH Pops.🙏🏽🏀
.
.
.
.
#marcusclick #blackhistorymonth #basketball #khof #ky #centralyellowjackets #louisvile #khsaa
